column2: It was wrong to sign anyone else. I refuse to see any other actor play in this role, especially since he was found not guilty and won his defamation lawsuit. Shame on you Disney! You will not get a dime of my money. Innocent until proven guilty!

column33: Bring Back Johnny Depp As Grindelwald in Fantastic Beasts
column34:
Johnny Depp has spent the last 6 years defamed, ousted from the life he worked so hard to build. Destroyed in a second by his toxic ex, spreading lies and misinformation in an attempt to bring this “powerful man” down to boost her own profile and bank balance, branding him as a “wife beater”, when all the evidence pointed at her, including many voice recordings of her admitting to physically abusing Johnny, whilst verbally, emotionally and psychologically abusing him.

In the furore of the U.K. defamation court case against The Sun newspaper in 2020, where Depp was branded a “wife-beater” due to Heard’s egregious claims, a single judge, and no jury to constitute a fair trial, ruled in Heard’s favour… with no evidence to substantiate her claims.

Warner Bros. turned their back on Johnny, forcing him to resign from his role as Gellert Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts franchise, regardless of the fact he swore not only his innocence but that he himself was the victim of domestic violence, at the hands of Amber Heard. 

On 1st June 2022, aptly World Narcissistic Abuse Awareness Day, Johnny won his defamation lawsuit against his ex, the jury reaching a unanimous verdict that he was defamed and she had indeed lied.

Johnny has proven his innocence and should now receive an apology from the studio and be reinstated in his role of Grindelwald for the final films in the franchise; Fantastic Beasts 4 & 5.

We, the undersigned, want Johnny Depp to be reinstated in his role of Gellert Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts franchise.
